## Vendor Notifications

This block adds vendor notifications: a bell icon in the navbar and a `GET /vendor/notifications` API endpoint.

### Notification Provider Setup

Configure the local notification provider in `medusa-config.ts` to include the `seller_feed` channel:

```ts
{
  resolve: '@medusajs/medusa/notification',
  options: {
    providers: [
      {
        resolve: '@medusajs/medusa/notification-local',
        id: 'local',
        options: {
          channels: ['feed', 'seller_feed']
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Middleware Setup

Add the vendor notification middlewares to your `api/middlewares.ts`:

```ts
import { defineMiddlewares } from "@medusajs/medusa";
import { vendorMiddlewares } from "./vendor/middlewares";

export default defineMiddlewares({
  routes: [...vendorMiddlewares],
});
```

### TopbarActions Component

Add the TopbarActions component to your `mercur.config.ts`:

```ts
export default {
  components: {
    TopbarActions: './components/topbar-actions'
  }
}
```

### Sending Notifications

To send vendor notifications from subscribers:

```ts
await notificationService.createNotifications({
  to: sellerId,
  channel: 'seller_feed',
  template: 'your-template',
  data: { title: 'New order', description: '...' }
})
```

### Run codegen

```bash
npx @mercurjs/cli@canary codegen
```

